                <h1>Exploring Feminism in the Yellow Wallpaper</h1>
                <p>The "Yellow Wallpaper" by Charlotte Perkins Gilman is a pivotal feminist text that explores the oppression of women in the 19th century. The protagonist's descent into madness symbolizes the effects of societal constraints on female identity and autonomy. This story reflects the struggle against patriarchal norms and advocates for women's liberation.</p>
